 be mezed again. That means, in order to do CC, you have one mez, then it must be split tanked. If a tank doesn't hit it when mez wears off, it will, of course, run straight to me or maybe the cleric if they did a lot of healing, and I won't be able to stop it. And once it has been hit, I won't be able to remez once the remez timer is up.<br>
<br>
The best CC will be root (which doesn't seem to have the reset timer) and park them out beyond melee range. Oddly enough that is what happened in Scars of Velious with the many unmezable mobs thus transforming enchanters from cc to buff machine (in some cases).<br>
<br>
